Package honeyroasted.jype.system

Class TypeSystem

java.lang.Object
honeyroasted.jype.system.TypeSystem
public class TypeSystem extends Object
This class represents a type system, along with a TypeCache. It allows creation of types from reflection values and TypeMirror values (for annotation processing). Additionally, it provides standard types such as NULL, all the primitives, their boxes, and the OBJECT class.

    • isAssignableTo

      public boolean isAssignableTo(TypeConcrete left, TypeConcrete right)
      Utilizes the ForceResolveTypeSolver to check if one type is assignable to the other. Note that ForceResolveTypeSolver may not work for all TypeConcretes. It is however guaranteed to work on type hierarchies with no unresolved TypeParameters.
      Parameters:
      left - The type to check if it can be assigned to right
      right - The type to check if left can be assigned to it
      Returns:
      true if left can be assigned to right

    • erasure

      public Optional<TypeConcrete> erasure(TypeConcrete type)
      Utilizes the ErasureTypeSolver to produce the TypeConcrete of the given type. The Java compiler erases certain generic type information to comply with backwards compatibility. This method will perform the same process on the given TypeConcrete.
      Parameters:
      type - The TypeConcrete to apply type erasure to
      Returns:
      An Optional containing the erased TypeConcrete, or empty if erasure could not be performed
